{"parentUuid":"7c7665a1-4ae5-4530-a230-887898ad4e33","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/ryan/formal-conjectures","sessionId":"72d36b6a-0e8d-4160-9892-aff5a0342b8f","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"ai-erdos-7","agentId":"a0676c1ff59266eb9","slug":"partitioned-doodling-deer","type":"progress","data":{"type":"hook_progress","hookEvent":"PostToolUse","hookName":"PostToolUse:Read","command":"callback"},"parentToolUseID":"toolu_016rvSDtK5PTd9BFjsfgCNgD","toolUseID":"toolu_016rvSDtK5PTd9BFjsfgCNgD","timestamp":"2026-03-09T22:09:29.656Z","uuid":"6bdf4d52-d35e-4883-a317-7be4eef8a88a"}
{"parentUuid":"7c7665a1-4ae5-4530-a230-887898ad4e33","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/ryan/formal-conjectures","sessionId":"72d36b6a-0e8d-4160-9892-aff5a0342b8f","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"ai-erdos-7","agentId":"a0676c1ff59266eb9","slug":"partitioned-doodling-deer","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016rvSDtK5PTd9BFjsfgCNgD","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/-\n     2→Copyright 2026 The Formal Conjectures Authors.\n     3→\n     4→Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→\n     8→    https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→\n    10→Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→limitations under the License.\n    15→-/\n    16→\n    17→import FormalConjectures.Util.ProblemImports\n    18→\n    19→/-!\n    20→# Erdős Problem 80\n    21→\n    22→*Reference:* [erdosproblems.com/80](https://www.erdosproblems.com/80)\n    23→\n    24→Let $c > 0$ and let $f_c(n)$ be the maximal $m$ such that every graph $G$ with\n    25→$n$ vertices and at least $cn^2$ edges, where each edge is contained in at least\n    26→one triangle, must contain a book of size $m$, that is, an edge shared by at least\n    27→$m$ different triangles.\n    28→\n    29→Estimate $f_c(n)$. In particular, is it true that $f_c(n) \\gg \\log n$?\n    30→\n    31→A problem of Erdős and Rothschild. Alon and Trotter showed that, provided $c < 1/4$,\n    32→$f_c(n) \\ll_c n^{1/2}$. Szemerédi observed that his regularity lemma implies\n    33→$f_c(n) \\to \\infty$. Fox and Loh proved that $f_c(n) \\le n^{O(1/\\log\\log n)}$ for\n    34→all $c < 1/4$, disproving the stronger conjecture $f_c(n) > n^\\varepsilon$.\n    35→\n    36→The weaker conjecture $f_c(n) \\gg \\log n$ remains open.\n    37→-/\n    38→\n    39→open SimpleGraph\n    40→\n    41→namespace Erdos80\n    42→\n    43→/-- The number of common neighbors of $u$ and $v$ in $G$, equivalently the number of\n    44→    triangles containing the edge $\\{u, v\\}$ (i.e., the book size at that edge). -/\n    45→def bookSize {V : Type*} [Fintype V] [DecidableEq V]\n    46→    (G : SimpleGraph V) [DecidableRel G.Adj] (u v : V) : ℕ :=\n    47→  ((G.neighborFinset u) ∩ (G.neighborFinset v)).card\n    48→\n    49→/-- Every edge of $G$ is contained in at least one triangle. -/\n    50→def EveryEdgeInTriangle {V : Type*} [Fintype V] [DecidableEq V]\n    51→    (G : SimpleGraph V) [DecidableRel G.Adj] : Prop :=\n    52→  ∀ u v : V, G.Adj u v → 0 < bookSize G u v\n    53→\n    54→/-- **Erdős Problem 80**: For every $c > 0$, there exists $C > 0$ such that every\n    55→    graph on $n$ vertices with at least $cn^2$ edges, where every edge lies in a\n    56→    triangle, contains an edge that is in at least $C \\log n$ triangles. -/\n    57→@[category research open, AMS 5]\n    58→theorem erdos_80 : answer(sorry) ↔\n    59→    ∀ c : ℝ, c > 0 →\n    60→    ∃ C : ℝ, C > 0 ∧\n    61→    ∀ (n : ℕ) (G : SimpleGraph (Fin n)) [DecidableRel G.Adj],\n    62→      (G.edgeFinset.card : ℝ) ≥ c * (n : ℝ) ^ 2 →\n    63→      EveryEdgeInTriangle G →\n    64→      ∃ u v : Fin n, G.Adj u v ∧\n    65→        (bookSize G u v : ℝ) ≥ C * Real.log (n : ℝ) := by\n    66→  sorry\n    67→\n    68→end Erdos80\n    69→"}]},"uuid":"48b50624-b9a6-48b5-bf1a-8093dec796f5","timestamp":"2026-03-09T22:09:29.655Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"7c7665a1-4ae5-4530-a230-887898ad4e33"}
